Acadamae Neophyte				NAMEISPI:YES	KEY:Trait ~ Acadamae Neophyte			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait			PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Acadamae Neophyte]																					SOURCEPAGE:p.10	DESC:Whenever you succeed at a Knowledge (planes) check to identify a creature and its special powers or vulnerabilities, you gain one additional piece of useful information (as if your skill check result had been 5 higher).
Binder's Blood							KEY:Trait ~ Binder's Blood			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait			PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Binder's Blood]																						SOURCEPAGE:p.10	DESC:You gain a +2 trait bonus on any Charisma-based checks when directly interacting with a genie.																																														BONUS:SITUATION|Bluff=Genies,Diplomacy=Genies,Intimidate=Genies,Sense Motive=Genies|2|TYPE=Trait
Expressive Pantomime						KEY:Trait ~ Expressive Pantomime		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait			PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Expressive Pantomime]																					SOURCEPAGE:p.10	DESC:You have learned to express yourself without having to depend on words. When attempting a Bluff check to deliver a secret message, you can take a –5 penalty on the check to communicate a simple message even to creatures that do not share a language with you. You cannot communicate with mindless creatures.
Hellknight Initiate			NAMEISPI:YES	KEY:Trait ~ Hellknight Initiate		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait			PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Hellknight Initiate]																					SOURCEPAGE:p.10	DESC:You gain a +2 trait bonus on damage rolls against outsiders summoned through conjuration (calling) and conjuration (summoning) spells and effects.																																					ASPECT:CombatBonus|+2 damage vs. summoned outsiders
Outsider Ties							KEY:Trait ~ Outsider Ties			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait			PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Outsider Ties]																						SOURCEPAGE:p.10	DESC:Choose a subtype of outsider, such as angel or elemental. When you summon an outsider of that subtype via summon monster, planar ally, planar binding, or similar spells and abilities, the summoned creature gains a number of temporary hit points equal to the level of spell used to summon it.
Vile Domain					DESCISPI:YES	KEY:Trait ~ Vile Domain				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait			PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Vile Domain]																						SOURCEPAGE:p.10	DESC:[NOT IMPLEMENTED] Choose a domain granted by an evil aligned deity, such as an archdevil, demon lord, or Great Old One. You gain a +1 trait bonus to your caster level when casting spells that are granted by that domain. This doesn't grant you the ability to cast such spells—you must still have access to the spells through some other means.

